In this video, I will show you how to use Google Assistant to search on Google without typing on your Android device. This is a hands-free feature useful for when you’re multitasking, driving, or just prefer using voice commands over typing for a quick Google search. With Google Assistant, you can easily perform searches and get information without typing anything.

Using Google Assistant for voice searches is really convenient. It allows you to search the web quickly and efficiently without the need for typing, making it convenient for various situations like cooking, exercising, or when you’re on the go. Voice searches are also more accessible for people with disabilities or those who find typing on a small screen difficult.

How to Search on Google Without Typing Using Google Assistant
In this step-by-step video tutorial, I show you how to use Google Assistant to perform voice searches on your Android device. 

You can activate Google Assistant using the "Hey Google" or "OK Google" voice commands or like I prefer by doing a long press on the Android circle home navigation button.

You can perform various types of searches, including web searches, location searches, and information retrieval, using voice commands.
Get more accurate search results by phrasing your voice commands clearly.

Other than performing voice searches, you can optimize your Google Assistant. You can customize voice settings, set up routines and use Google Assistant to control compatible smart devices in your home. Make the most out of Google Assistant and enhance your overall user experience.

The new Gemini AI features more advanced uses and it includes Google Assistant functions too.
